{RESULTS}: The vaccine was well tolerated, with no difference in adverse event frequency among 95 vaccinees vs 102 placebo recipients. The primary endpoint, moderate (≥3.0 L) to severe (≥5.0 L) diarrheal purge, occurred in 39 of 66 (59.1\%) placebo controls but only 2 of 35 (5.7\%) vaccinees at 10 days (vaccine efficacy, 90.3\%; P {\textless} .0001) and 4 of 33 (12.1\%) vaccinees at 3 months (vaccine efficacy, 79.5\%; P {\textless} .0001).
